    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Red-Black Tree</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            background-color: #f0f0f0;\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n        }\n\n        .container {\n            max-width: 800px;\n            margin: 40px auto;\n            padding: 20px;\n            background-color: #fff;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            border-radius: 10px;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n        }\n\n        .section {\n            margin-bottom: 40px;\n        }\n\n        .section h2 {\n            font-weight: bold;\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\n        }\n\n        .section p {\n            font-size: 16px;\n            color: #666;\n        }\n\n        .button {\n            padding: 10px 20px;\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            background-color: #4CAF50;\n            color: #fff;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            transition: background-color 0.3s ease-in-out;\n        }\n\n        .button:hover {\n            background-color: #3e8e41;\n        }\n\n        .graph {\n            position: relative;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100vh;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n        }\n\n        .graph canvas {\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h1>Red-Black Tree</h1>\n        <p>Visual Representation of Red-Black Tree Data Structure</p>\n\n        <div class=\"section\">\n            <h2>Node Properties</h2>\n            <p>The following properties are used to construct a Red-Black Tree:\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Color (Red or Black): Indicates the color of the node.</li>\n                    <li>Left Child: The node to the left of the current node.</li>\n                    <li>Right Child: The node to the right of the current node.</li>\n                    <li>Parent: The parent node of the current node.</li>\n                    <li>Height: The height of the tree.</li>\n                </ul>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"section\">\n            <h2>Insertion Order</h2>\n            <p>Insertion order is the order in which nodes are inserted into the tree. The tree is always sorted in ascending order.</p>\n\n            <canvas id=\"graph\"></canvas>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"section\">\n            <h2>Traversal Order</h2>\n            <p>Traversal order is the order in which nodes are visited during a traversal of the tree. The tree is always traversed in ascending order.</p>\n\n            <canvas id=\"graph\"></canvas>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"section\">\n            <h2>Red-Black Tree Properties</h2>\n            <p>The following properties are used to construct a Red-Black Tree:\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Each node has a color (Red or Black).</li>\n                    <li>The root node is always Black.</li>\n                    <li>The left and right children of a node are either Black or Red.</li>\n                </ul>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        let graph = document.getElementById('graph');\n        let ctx = graph.getContext('2d');\n        let colors = ['red', 'black'];\n\n        function drawNode(x, y, color) {\n            ctx.beginPath();\n            ctx.arc(x, y, 20, 0, 2 * Math.PI);\n            ctx.fillStyle = color;\n            ctx.fill();\n        }\n\n        function drawTree(x, y, color, level) {\n            drawNode(x, y, color);\n            ctx.fillStyle = colors[level];\n            ctx.fillRect(x, y, 20, 20);\n            ctx.fillStyle = color;\n            ctx.font = '16px Arial';\n            ctx.textAlign = 'center';\n            ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';\n            ctx.fillText(`Level: ${level}`, x + 10, y + 10);\n        }\n\n        function insertNode(x, y, color) {\n            drawTree(x, y, color, 0);\n            let radius = 20;\n            for (let i = 1; i < 4; i++) {\n                radius += 10;\n            }\n            for (let i = 0; i < 4; i++) {\n                let angle = i * Math.PI / 2;\n                let x1 = x + radius * Math.cos(angle);\n                let y1 = y + radius * Math.sin(angle);\n                let x2 = x + radius * Math.cos(angle + Math.PI / 2);\n                let y2 = y + radius * Math.sin(angle + Math.PI / 2);\n                drawNode(x1, y1, colors[i % colors.length]);\n                drawNode(x2, y2, colors[i % colors.length]);\n            }\n        }\n\n        function traverse(x, y, color) {\n            drawTree(x, y, color, 1);\n            ctx.fillStyle = color;\n            ctx.font = '16px Arial';\n            ctx.textAlign = 'center';\n            ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';\n            ctx.fillText('Left', x + 10, y + 10);\n            ctx.fillText('Right', x + 50, y + 10);\n        }\n\n        function redBlackTree(x, y) {\n            insertNode(x, y, 'black');\n            traverse(x, y, 'black');\n        }\n\n        redBlackTree(100, 100);\n    </script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
